5:
Come with me, Luca. There's
something I wish to show you.
9:
Why did you bring me to a place like
this?
12:
Because I NEED you, Luca. You are
absolutely essential to my plans.
15:
The child of Captain Zegra... Do you
not realize that you have been
chosen?
17:
No matter. It's time. Let's go.
Your father is waiting.
21:
Rather dark, isn't it. This should make
things a bit clearer.
30:
Now, now. There's no need to
whimper and quiver like that. Every
single one of these specimens is like
family to you, after all.
37:
In the strictest sense of the
word—you have genetic material in
common, mutated though some of
it may be. Of course, they are purely
imitations.
39:
They're merely creatures forcibly
implanted with the Captain's genes.
You, on the other hand, are his only
real, flesh and blood heir.
42: What are you trying to say?
45:
What, did you think Captain Zegra's
treasure was some chest filled with
trinkets and dubloons? His real
treasure is his legacy...
47:
He discovered a forbidden
power—one which the ancient
people of this world once held. The
ability to become something more.
49:
The key to transcending the limits of
humanity!
54:
I... I don't care about any of that!
What happened to my father?
Where is he?
58:
Let me see him! I need to talk with
him and ask him...
Why he...
64:
I see. Why not ask him for yourself,
then? He's right there, after all.
68:
It's been five long years since you
left us, Captain... But here we are, at
the bottom of the ocean, finally
reunited.
70:
He had already broken free from the
fetters of humanity, you know. But it
seems even that wasn't enough.
Something was missing.
74:
No... I don't believe you. I don't
believe he would do something like—
78:
Oh really? Why do you think you
were led here, then? Was it not his
voice that called to you?
80:
He needed you, Luca.
To me, that suggests that you are
the final piece of the puzzle.
85: What's going on? Let me go!
93:
Please, Luca. Just do this one thing
for us, wouldn't you?
99:
There are many possible
approaches here. An application of
a curse on Liquid Genome, for
instance... Or—
118: Let's get out of here, Luca!
126:
I'm sorry, Luca... It wasn't supposed
to be me who came to save you... It
should have been Marina.
134:
It's all right. Everything's going to be
fine!
137:
Listen. We're gonna get out of here...
We'll make it back to the others in no
time.
